A set of scripts to interact with the affiliation disambiguation tool.

Author: Benoit Thiell <bthiell@cfa.harvard.edu>
License: GPL

== Institution searcher ==

Here is an example of how to use the functionality as a library:

    In [1]: import institution_searcher

    In [2]: institution_searcher.get_best_matches('CERN, Geneva')
    Out[2]: u'902725'

Here is an example of how to use the functionality as a script:

    $ ./institution_searcher.py 'CERN, Geneva'
    902725
